# Cursor AI Rules
# See: https://docs.cursor.com/context/rules-for-ai

## Project Context
This repository is a curated collection of configuration files and instructions for AI coding agents.
Read AGENTS.md for the canonical coding guidelines before making any changes.

## General Rules
- Make the smallest possible change that fully addresses the task.
- Match the style and conventions already present in the file being edited.
- Do not modify files unrelated to the current task.
- Do not commit secrets, credentials, or sensitive data.

## Code Style
- Use descriptive, explicit names over short abbreviations.
- Keep functions small and focused on a single responsibility.
- Use 2-space indentation for JSON files.
- Use GitHub Flavored Markdown for all `.md` files.

## Commit Messages
Use Conventional Commits format: feat:, fix:, docs:, chore:, refactor:, test:

## File Structure
Follow the directory structure documented in README.md.
New AI agent config files belong at the repo root or inside their designated directory.
